snippet.textDisplay:
Jenna is correct, it is much more runny than the original recipe which is more custardy BUT the important part here is that the taste was there and the fun!
Julien, if you wish to make Jenna happy with a more green crème brûlée, it is possible if you add some green alcohol. I remember having a crème brûlée made with "Chartreuse" which is a green-looking French liqueur tasting like anise. Adding any good-tasting liqueur to your crème brûlée is always a good idea to explore...
